quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  16,94,"And do not make your oaths a means of mischief among yourselves, lest a foot should slip after it is firmly placed, and you taste evil for your having prevented (others) from the path of Allah, and for you there be a great punishment."
  16,95,"And do not take a paltry price against the pledge of Allah. Indeed, what is with Allah is much better for you, if but you knew."
  16,96,"What is with you shall end and what is with Allah shall last. And certainly, We shall give those who observed patience their reward for the good they used to do."
  16,97,"Whoever, male or female, has done righteous deed, while a believer, We shall certainly make him live a good life and shall give such people their reward for the good they used to do."
  16,98,"So, when you recite the Qur'an, seek the protection of Allah against Satan, the accursed."
  16,99,"He is such that he has no power over those who believe and place trust in their Lord."
  16,100,"His power is only over those who be-friend him and those who associate partners with Him."
  16,101,"And when We replace a verse with another verse - and Allah knows best what He reveals - they say, "You are but a forger." Instead, most of them do not know."
  16,102,"Say, 'This has been brought down by Ruh al-Qudus (the Holy Spirit – Jibra’ il) from your Lord rightly (as due), so that it makes the believers firm and becomes guidance and good news for the Muslims."